Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Halve @Poblano Pepper{2} lengthwise; remove stems and seeds. Drizzle each half with @Vegetable Oil{4%teaspoon}; season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Place on a #baking sheet{} and roast on middle rack until softened, ~{15-17%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil; cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. While rice cooks, dice @Yellow Onion{1}(diced) and @Roma Tomato{1}(diced). Zest and quarter @Lime{1} (for 4, zest 1 lime; quarter both). Mince @Chili Pepper{1}(minced). In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, salt, pepper, and lime zest to taste. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

> The crema is meant to be drizzled over the finished dish for a zesty kick.

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably ovenproof, pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1}, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, half the tomato, and @water{2%tablespoon} (¼ cup for 4 servings); season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir cooked rice into pan with veggies until thoroughly combined. Return pan to medium-high heat. Stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Turn off heat. Season with salt and pepper.

Once poblanos are roasted, stuff each half with as much filling as will fit. Nestle into pan with remaining filling.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer remaining filling to a small baking dish and arrange stuffed poblanos in there.

Sprinkle poblano halves with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/2%cup}. Bake until cheese is melted and slightly crisp at edges, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, toss remaining tomato in a second small bowl with a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper. Divide filling and stuffed poblanos between plates. Top with @Guacamole{4%tablespoon}, seasoned tomato, crema, and chili if desired. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.